    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team determined that the CFD hemolysis model demonstrates sufficient credibility for regulatory submission under the condition that the documented credibility gaps (relevance of validation activities, model form uncertainty, equivalency of input parameters, use error review, test samples) are addressed in a follow-on assessment prior to final device clearance. The absolute NIH predictions are within acceptable error bounds at four of five operating points. The Monte Carlo UQ provides adequate characterisation of coefficient uncertainty. The package is accepted at Low assurance level with open credibility factor gaps formally recorded.",
